benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/customFields - Retrieve invoice item custom fields

covered: Valid Request scenarios are covered by TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC12, TC13, TC14, TC15, TC19, TC22
Empty Response scenario covered by TC04 (empty array when no custom fields)
Query Parameters variations covered by TC05, TC11, TC19
Error handling scenarios covered by TC06, TC07, TC08, TC09, TC10, TC16, TC17, TC18, TC20, TC21
Performance/Concurrency scenarios covered by TC15 (concurrency) and TC16 (timeout)
Backward compatibility and versioning considerations covered by TC14
Integration with dependent services covered by TC20
Security and input validation scenarios covered by TC10 and TC21
Response structure and machine-readable JSON covered by TC22
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests for server-side pagination handling with large datasets
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache validation
Rate Limiting: No tests asserting behavior under high request rate or throttling
Limited coverage of 504/timeout scenarios beyond TC16
Less explicit coverage for 401/403 beyond TC08 (could include broader authorization edge cases)
Edge-case malformed path handling (e.g., missing invoiceItemId in path) beyond TC18
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests to verify proper page size, page tokens, and total counts when retrieving large numbers of custom fields
Add tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and cache validation behavior
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to ensure the API gracefully handles burst of requests
Enhance authorization coverage with additional 401/403 edge cases and token expiry scenarios
Add test cases for additional malformed path inputs and edge-case URL constructions to strengthen input validation
